==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wire-wound gun
<hw>Wire"-wound` gun</hw>. <fld>(Ordnance)</fld> <def>A gun in the
construction of which an inner tube (either entire or in segments) is
wound with wire under tension to insure greater soundness and uniformity
of resistance. In modern construction hoops and jackets are shrunk on
over the wire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wiriness</ent>⟦br⟧
